        {
          "name": "User Preferences & Settings",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Fetch Onboarding Languages",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/onboarding/languages", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "onboarding", "languages"]},
                "description": "Fetch list of available languages for onboarding. Can be called during signup to pre-populate language selection.\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"languages\": [\n      {\"code\": \"es\", \"name\": \"Spanish\"},\n      {\"code\": \"fr\", \"name\": \"French\"},\n      {\"code\": \"de\", \"name\": \"German\"},\n      {\"code\": \"zh\", \"name\": \"Mandarin\"},\n      {\"code\": \"ja\", \"name\": \"Japanese\"}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 401: Unauthorized (missing/invalid access token)"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Fetch Onboarding Professions",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/onboarding/professions", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "onboarding", "professions"]},
                "description": "Fetch list of available professions for onboarding. Can be called during signup to pre-populate profession selection.\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"professions\": [\n      {\"id\": \"software_engineer\", \"name\": \"Software Engineer\"},\n      {\"id\": \"data_scientist\", \"name\": \"Data Scientist\"},\n      {\"id\": \"product_manager\", \"name\": \"Product Manager\"},\n      {\"id\": \"designer\", \"name\": \"Designer\"},\n      {\"id\": \"marketing\", \"name\": \"Marketing Specialist\"}\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 401: Unauthorized (missing/invalid access token)"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get User Preferences",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/preferences", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "preferences"]},
                "description": "Retrieve user's current preferences (base language, profession, location).\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"preferences\": {\n      \"baseLanguage\": \"en\",\n      \"profession\": \"software_engineer\",\n      \"location\": \"Lagos\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 401: Unauthorized (missing/invalid access token)\n- 404: User not found"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Update User Preferences",
              "request": {
                "method": "PUT",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"baseLanguage\": \"en\",\n  \"profession\": \"software_engineer\",\n  \"location\": \"San Francisco\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/preferences", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "preferences"]},
                "description": "Update user preferences (base language, profession, location). All fields optional.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `baseLanguage` (string, optional): User's native/base language code (e.g., 'en', 'es', 'fr')\n- `profession` (string, optional): User's profession (e.g., 'software_engineer')\n- `location` (string, optional): User's geographic location\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"preferences\": {\n      \"baseLanguage\": \"en\",\n      \"profession\": \"software_engineer\",\n      \"location\": \"San Francisco\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 400: Bad request (invalid field values)\n- 401: Unauthorized\n- 404: User not found"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Get User Settings",
              "request": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/settings", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "settings"]},
                "description": "Retrieve user's security and notification settings including 2FA status.\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"settings\": {\n      \"notifications\": {\n        \"inAppEnabled\": true,\n        \"emailEnabled\": true\n      },\n      \"security\": {\n        \"twoFactorEnabled\": false,\n        \"twoFactorMethod\": null\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 401: Unauthorized\n- 404: User not found"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Update Notification Settings",
              "request": {
                "method": "PATCH",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"inAppEnabled\": true,\n  \"emailEnabled\": false\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/settings/notifications", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "settings", "notifications"]},
                "description": "Update notification preferences. Both fields optional.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `inAppEnabled` (boolean, optional): Enable/disable in-app notifications\n- `emailEnabled` (boolean, optional): Enable/disable email notifications\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"notifications\": {\n      \"inAppEnabled\": true,\n      \"emailEnabled\": false\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 400: Bad request (invalid field types)\n- 401: Unauthorized\n- 404: User not found"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Start 2FA Setup",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "body": {"mode": "raw", "raw": ""},
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/2fa/setup", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "2fa", "setup"]},
                "description": "Initiate 2FA setup process. Sends a 6-digit OTP via email.\n\n**Request Body**: Empty (no body required)\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"message\": \"2FA verification code sent to your email. It expires in 10 minutes.\",\n    \"method\": \"email\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Dev Mode**: In development, OTP is printed to console logs.\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 401: Unauthorized (missing/invalid access token)\n- 404: User not found (account deleted or invalid)\n- 409: Conflict (2FA already enabled, disable first)\n- 500: SMTP error if email service unconfigured (dev: falls back to console logging)"
              }
            },
            {
              "name": "Verify 2FA Setup",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json"}, {"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}"
                },
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/2fa/verify", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "2fa", "verify"]},
                "description": "Verify 2FA setup by submitting OTP received via email. Enables 2FA on the account.\n\n**Request Body**:\n- `otp` (string, required): 6-digit OTP from email (check console.log in dev)\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"twoFactorEnabled\": true,\n    \"method\": \"email\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow**:\n1. Call POST /auth/2fa/setup to send OTP\n2. Copy OTP from email (or console in dev)\n3. Call this endpoint with the OTP within 10 minutes\n4. 2FA is now active and will be required on next login\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 400: Bad request (invalid OTP format or OTP expired)\n- 401: Unauthorized\n- 404: User not found\n- 422: Unprocessable entity (OTP incorrect or mismatch)\n- 500: Failed to enable 2FA"
              },
              "event": [
                {
                  "listen": "test",
                  "script": {
                    "type": "text/javascript",
                    "exec": [
                      "pm.test('2FA setup verification successful', function () { pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200); });",
                      "try {",
                      "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                      "  if (json?.data?.twoFactorEnabled) pm.collectionVariables.set('2fa_enabled', 'true');",
                      "} catch (error) {",
                      "  console.log('Error parsing 2FA response', error);",
                      "}"
                    ]
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "name": "Disable 2FA",
              "request": {
                "method": "DELETE",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{access_token}}"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{base_url}}/auth/2fa", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["auth", "2fa"]},
                "description": "Disable 2FA on user's account. Clears all 2FA-related data.\n\n**Request Body**: Empty (no body required)\n\n**Response Example (200)**:\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"message\": \"Two-factor authentication has been disabled\",\n    \"twoFactorEnabled\": false\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Impact**: Once disabled, 2FA will not be required on next login unless re-enabled.\n\n**Error Cases**:\n- 401: Unauthorized (missing/invalid access token)\n- 404: User not found\n- 500: Failed to disable 2FA"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
